=== Chapter VI: Symbols in Alchemy

#hm-note[
  Albertus provides a complete glossary of Rosicrucian alchemical symbols, noting that the Rosicrucian fraters used these sacred symbols to prevent alchemical, mystical, or occult secrets from falling into the hands of those who would misuse them. "To those who are able to understand them, they possess an honorable and even a holy significance." No claim is made that the symbols reproduced are the only ones used. Some alchemists devised their own sets when formerly used signs fell into the hands of charlatans.
]

==== I: Signs of the Four Elements
- Fire (Ignis) — upward triangle
- Air (Aer) — upward triangle with horizontal bar
- Water (Aqua) — downward triangle
- Earth (Terra) — downward triangle with horizontal bar

==== II: Signs of Metals and Planets
- Mercury (Argentum vivum) — ☿ | Tin / Jupiter (Stannum) — ♃ | Copper / Venus (Cuprum) — ♀
- Silver / Moon (Argentum / Luna) — ☽ | Gold / Sun (Sol) — ☉ | Iron / Mars (Ferrum) — ♂ | Lead / Saturn (Plumbum) — ♄

==== III: Signs of Minerals
Antimony, Sulfur, Cinnabar, Lead Monoxide (Lithargium), Talc, Marcasite, Magnet / Lodestone, Arsenic, Gold Pigment, Alum, Soda (Nitrum), Salt, Saltpeter (Sal praeparatum), Vitriol, Lime / Chalk (Calx), Green of Copper (Viride Aeris — copper chelate), Quicklime (Calx viva), Sand (Arena).

==== IV: Products of Minerals
Brass (Aurichalcum), Glass of Talc or Hematite (Specular), Refined Mercury (Mercurius Sublimatus), Amalgam / Mercury Solid (Mercurius praecipitatus), Pure Metal (Regulus), Iron Filings (Limatura Martis), Zinc Carbonate or Oxide (Tutia), Red Lead Oxide (Miny), Lead Acetate (Cerussa), Oxide of a Metal (Flores), Black Ink (Attramentum), Pure Quicksilver (Mercurius vita).

==== V: Signs of Vegetables
- Potassium Bitartrate (Tartarus) | Potassium Carbonate (Sal tartari) | Ashes (Cinis) | Crude Potassium Carbonate (Cinceres Clavellati) | Liquor (Lixivium)
- Vinegar (Acetum) | Distilled Vinegar (Acetum Distillatum) | Alcohol Solution (Spiritus) | Spirits of Wine (Spiritus vini) | Rectified Spirits of Wine (Spiritus vini Root)
- Wax (Cera) | Sugar (Sacharum) | Camphor | Herb (Herba) | Roots (Radices) | Gum (Gumi)

==== VI: Signs of Animals
Urine (Urina), Hart's Horn / Ammonium Carbonate (Cornua Cervi), Crab (Cancer), Lion (Leo), Virgin (Virgo), Ape / Scales (Simia / Libra), Scorpion, Archbearer, Goat/Capricorn (Caper), Pitcher/Vase (Amphora), Fish (Pisces), Twins (Gemini), Bull (Taurus), Ram (Aries).

==== VII: Signs of Time
Year (Annus), Month (Mensis), Time / Hour (Hora), Day (Dies), Night (Nox).

==== VIII: Signs of Weight
Pound (Libra / Scales), Ounce (Uncia), Half Ounce, Drachma (1/8 oz), Drachma ¾ (1/16 oz), Scrupulus (1/24 oz — 20 grams), Scrupulus ¾ (1/48 oz), Grain (Grana), Drop (Gutta), Equal Parts of Each (Ana), Sufficient Quantity (Quantum Satis), Handful (Manipulus).

==== IX: Signs of Instruments
Glass Container (Alembicum Vitrum), Retort (Retorta), Receiver (Vas recipiens), Crucible (Crucibulus), Water Bath (Balneum Mariae), Steam Bath (Balneum Vaporis), Furnace (Ignis Circulator).

==== X: Signs of Operations
Sublimate (Sublimare), Precipitate (Precipitare), Filter (Filtrare), Amalgamate (Amalgamare), Digest — heat in water or moderate heat (Digestio), Mud of Otter (Luto Lutrine — a type of luting/sealing clay), Solution (Solvere), Layer upon Layer (Stratum super Stratum), Extract (Extrahere), Distil (Distillare), Evaporate (Evaporare).

